HOUSE RESOLUTION 64
By Glynn
A RESOLUTION to commend Yamia Ward for exemplary service
as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this body is pleased to recognize certain persons
who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Yamia Ward is one such individual who has distinguished herself in her role
as a legislative intern for Representative Ronnie Glynn; Ms. Ward's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a senior at Fisk University, where she is highly regarded by her peers, Ms.
Ward has achieved academic success while majoring in political science and participating in
numerous extracurricular activities, including serving as the president of the political science
club; and
WHEREAS, during her time at Fisk University, Ms. Ward has developed a strong
passion for advocacy, a desire to effect positive change in her community, and an aspiration to
become a civil rights attorney; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Yamia Ward brought her many abilities
and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2025 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth
General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2025 legislative session, Ms. Ward has surpassed all criteria
that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Yamia Ward has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby
